name: Narissa Tsuboi
bio: Nars lives in West Seattle with her partner and two energetic pomeranians. She spends her time learning to code, working as a project manager, and spending time with friends on Alki Beach. You can find her on Sunday's at the West Seattle farmers market!

name: Nirmalya Ghosh
bio: Nirmalya is from New Delhi, India and came to Seattle to pursue higher education in 2016. He has been a Seattleite ever since. Nirmalya enjoys finding new places to eat and loves hiking during the summer. His favorite park is Green Lake where he likes to hammock and relax.

name: Nuli Bang
bio: Nuli came to Seattle from Seoul, South Korea in 2019 and now lives with four cats. She loves to explore new restaurants and taste hidden delicacies. She's into discovering delicious Chinese restaurants and dessert shops these days, and if you are interested in the same thing, enjoy it with her!

name: Evan Marshall
bio: Evan is from Miami, Florida and arrived to Seattle in 2018 when his parents found new jobs in the city. He enjoys checking out new vegetarian restaurants and crate digging at his local record store. His favorite places are the Egyptian Movie theater in Capitol Hill and the restaurant Lost on Mars.

name: Zi Wang
bio: Zi is from Edmonton, Alberta, Canada and came to Seattle in 2020. She enjoys exploring the myriad of restaurants across the city to indulge her appetite for dim sum and hot pot. She also likes to go finding nemo at the Seattle Aquarium, stroll along Discovery Park beach, and snap photos at the Washington Park Arboretum!
